### 19.

1\. Now at that time Ro*g*a the Malla was a friend of the venerable
Ânanda's <span id="fr_421"></span>[1](#fn_413.md). And a linen cloth
belonging to Ro*g*a the Malla had been deposited in the keeping of the
venerable Ânanda; and the venerable Ânanda had need of a linen cloth.

They told this matter to the Blessed One.

'I allow you, O Bhikkhus, to take a thing on trust (that it would be
given to you) when it belongs to a person possessed of these five
qualifications--he must be an intimate and familiar friend who has been
spoken to (about it) <span id="fr_422"></span>[2](#fn_414.md) and is alive,
(and the Bhikkhu taking the thing) must know "He will remain pleased
with me after I have taken it." I allow you, O Bhikkhus, to take a thing
on trust (that it would be given to you) <span
id="fr_423"></span>[3](#fn_415.md) when it belongs to a person possessed of
these five qualifications.'

